cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.CV, cs.CR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on the impact of demand splitting over heterogeneous processing resources in an IoT platform, supported by Fog and Cloud infrastructure. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also likely as the paper discusses the gains of splitting resource intensive demands among IoT nodes, Fog devices and Cloud servers. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper evaluates the impact of distributed processing on power consumption for IoT-based surveillance applications. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is a possible category as the paper considers a surveillance application consisting of multiple smart cameras capable of capturing and analyzing real-time video streams. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is a less likely category as the paper does not focus on security or cryptography, but it may be relevant in the context of IoT security.
